Shocked residents at the scene a Manoti Mobero, 90, was killed. [ Stanley Ongwae, Standard]  A man said to be mentally ill was lynched in Sononkora village, Nyamira County, on Tuesday after he reportedly killed a 90-year-old man.  Maxwell Nyakundi, 40, is said to have attacked Manoti Mobero with a machete killing him on the spot.    Confirming the incident, area chief Livingston Mabuka said the 90-year-old suffered deep cuts.   Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. "Nyakundi was walking when he met and attacked Mobero. The elderly man was found unconscious and later succumbed to his injuries,” Mabuka said.  Farmers in dilemma as moles ravage food fields in Nyamira  Governor to work with anti-graft body to nab corrupt county staff  90-year old anklets that have weathered cultural transitions  Chebilat town’s steady growth 13 years after post-election violence Nyakundi tried to hide in a neighbour's house after the attack but was flushed out by angry villagers and lynched.  According to a resident Kepha Nyasimi, Nyukundi struggled with mental illness and would turn violent at times.  "He [Nyakundi] has assaulted many people. We had, however, not lost a life until this latest attack,” said another villager, Duke Oichoe.   Maiti yafukuliwa kisii baada ya mahakama kutoa agizo  Man kills wife and chops body parts in Nyamira County  Mke apatikana na makosa ya uzinzi mjini Nyamira By Julius Chepkwony | 3 hours ago By Lydiah Nyawira | 4 hours ago By Stanley Ongwae | 5 hours ago By Joackim Bwana | 8 hours ago